section.title: Chief Complaint And Reason For Visit

td.paragraph:
Referred To: Peter Dziegielewski 1600 S.W. Archer Road
Box 100264 Gainesville, FL +1-8698172308 Ordered: Referrals: Otolaryngology. Peter Dziegielewski. Evaluate and treat Appointment date/timeframe: {referrals_order_.apptTimeframe}

td.content: Pertinent negatives include abdominal pain, chest pain, constipation, dysuria, increased thirst, night sweats, weight gain and weight loss. Additional information: Pt is here as a referral follow up. He has a history of tonsil cancer.

To recap, Mr. Chambers has a history of Stage IVA (T2N2bM0) SCC of L OP, for which he received concurrent chemo-radiation which he completed in 2016-08-17. Less than 6 months later within 2016 he developed right upper lobe lung metastasis which was treated with stereotactic body radiotherapy. Fortunately since then he has been cancer free until now. Patient states that his neck has been hurting he was having trouble sleeping. So, patient had a PET/CT ordered & performed on oct 31st with an FDG avid L neck lymph node with SUV of 4.7. FNA was ordered by Dr. Marina (rad onc) which was positive for SCC. Patient just saw Dr. Jain (med onc) who has offered him palliative chemo should he choose to defer surgery. No other obvious disease on the scan other than the L neck. He has received no treatments for this new cancer to date.

Pt reports his throat is extremely painful. His neck also hurts at times. Pt continues to struggle with breathing when laying down. Pt reports he has had soem improvement in the breathing. Pt has not been taking omeprazole as directed.

Pt states that he is done w/ his radiation for now. Pt states that he has chest, and throat pain. He states he is having difficulty breathing, especially when he lies down . Pt states that he is out of his percocet that was prescribed by Dr. Marina.

Onset: 2 years ago. Duration: 2 Years. Location is left upper neck. The patient describes it as tender. It occurs constantly. The size of the neck mass is increasing. Context: prolonged tobacco use. Pertinent negatives include dysphagia, dyspnea, fever, hoarseness, pain in/around ear and pharyngitis. Additional information: Has also lost weight recently unintentionally. Saw Dr. Jain today & we were asked to see emergently.
